How do we test this? What is the problem?

class Document
{
    String html;

    public Document(String url)
    {
        var client = new HtmlClient();
        html = client.get(url);
    }
}

----------------------------------------------------

What is the problem here?

class Document
{
    String html;

    public Document(HtmlClient client, String url)
    {
        html = client.get(url);
    }
}

Law of Demeter: do not ask for something you need directly
only to get to what you really want.

Ex: obj1.getSomething
        .getSomethingElse
        .getTheOtherThing
        .getWhatIReallyWant;

----------------------------------------------------

Use factories!

class Document
{
    String html;

    public Document(String html)
    {
        this.html = html;
    }
}

class DocumentFactory
{
    HtmlClient client;

    public DocumentFactory(HtmlClient client)
    {
        this.client = client;
    }

    public Document build(String url)
    {
        return new Document(client.get(url));
    }
}

